&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Click on the elements that show the &quot;drill down&quot; decorator ( &lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;./resources/Drill%20Down-33.jpg&quot;&#xD;
    width=&quot;12&quot; height=&quot;12&quot; />&amp;nbsp;) to see more detail.&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This diagram is the root of the EA level Business Process Model, containing the definitions or linking to the various&#xD;
    diagrams that define this aspect. ThuNorTech has the usual corporate management activities as well as&#xD;
    corporate&amp;nbsp;services. The two &quot;Business Lines&quot; (BL) of ThuNorTech, as shown above,&amp;nbsp;are &quot;IT Research&quot; and &quot;IT&#xD;
    Solutions&quot;.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <keyConsiderations>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Layers are added to create a hierarchy with&amp;nbsp;more detailed views of the activity provided as you drill down.&#xD;
    Clicking on the activity (as noted above) takes you to this nested diagram. This same approach is used to link to&#xD;
    the&amp;nbsp;'leaf activities' that are form the basis for the logical model at the completion of the business level&#xD;
    Process Model, and which form the top layer of the Logical Process Model.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Layering the process model to deal with complexity is of value. Start with a top layer of activities that are&#xD;
    abstractions of larger constructs, with the next layer of detail showing more detailed activities. This&#xD;
    top-level&amp;nbsp;diagram is used to hide complexity, so these activities&amp;nbsp;should be viewed as only a very simple&#xD;
    start at understanding and documenting the business.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    There are four separate areas described within the Business: Enterprise Management, Corporate Services, the IT Research&#xD;
    BL and the IT Solutions BL. The main Actors are shown along with the Internet Domain, which is an important part of how&#xD;
    ThuNorTech does business.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Note:&lt;/strong> At the enterprise (EA) level this top-down model of the organization is based upon a Business&#xD;
    Function view. That is, the major functional areas of the organization are identified such as Executive Management,&#xD;
    Financial Management, Human Resources, and in this case the two business lines &quot;IT Research&quot; and &quot;IT Solutions&quot;. Lower&#xD;
    level architectures work best if switched to a &quot;service&quot; viewpoint: the services (and products) provided to Customers.&#xD;
&lt;/p></keyConsiderations>
